President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump will be visiting Japan, South Korea, China, Vietnam, the Philippines, and Hawaii from November 3-14, 2017. During this trip, the President will participate in various bilateral, multilateral, and cultural events, including the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation summit and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations summit. The purpose of the trip is to demonstrate the United States' commitment to its alliances and partnerships in the region, as well as to discuss the importance of a free and open Indo-Pacific region for America's prosperity and security. The President will also emphasize the need for fair and reciprocal economic ties with trade partners. Additionally, the trip aims to strengthen international resolve in addressing the North Korean threat and achieving the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.